ail is beginner to intermediate with some technical areas. We had already hiked a portion along the North Shore Lake Hodges Trail from I-15 to Del Dios Community Park, and the segment through… Dogs are also able to use this trail but must be kept on leash. The Lake Hodges Bicycle Pedestrian Bridge and surrounding area is part of the San Dieguito River Park. 18448 W Bernardo Dr, San Diego, California 92127. Check out some of our favorite hiking guides for San Diego County: Way Up Trail/Lake Hodges Overlook (Elfin Forest Recreational Reserve), This Week in San Diego Hiking – February 11, 2019, This Week in San Diego Hiking – February 4, 2019, This Week in San Diego Hiking – January 28, 2019, This Week in San Diego Hiking – January 14, 2019, This Week in San Diego Hiking – January 7, 2019, None at trailhead; Port-a-potties at various points on the trail. The Lake Hodges 50K is a deceptively challenging course, ideal for all running levels. Western and Clark’s grebes are already coming back in number; look for their rushing display, where a pair of grebes rears up and runs, side by side, across the surface of the water without even moving their wings. Around 1.1 miles we encountered an unmarked “Y” junction. Just beyond was the stress-ribbon bridge spanning the lake and a bike repair station. As you enter the trailhead, stay right on San Dieguito trail. Trail Map of the area. Invite. It was completed in 1918, and later purchased by the city of San Diego. The trail is primarily used for hiking, walking, running, and mountain biking and is accessible year-round. March 30, 2020 Brenda Miller *** LAKE HODGES AND THE TRAILS SURROUNDING THE LAKE ARE CLOSED PER CITY OF SAN DIEGO MANDATE *** This is a reminder that all City of San Diego reservoirs are closed. Hodges Lake Staff: 9-14-2020: Weather Has Cooled and Fish Are Biting More Actively The weather has cooled down and the fish... more » Hodges Lake Staff: 8-31-2020: Hodges Reservoir Fishing Report Bass have been caught freq